title: 2024 Hyundai Tucson N Line - The Best SUV Ever
article:
Is the 2024 Hyundai Tucson a Good SUV?
Yes, the 2024 Tucson is an excellent SUV. Its spacious, upscale interior seats five in near-luxury-level comfort, the in-car tech is easy to use, and standard features are abundant. The Tucson glides confidently, whether on straight, patchy highways or gentle winding roads, and it has one of the largest cargo capacities among compact SUVs. It also cuts a pretty dashing figure in a sea of more conservatively styled competitors, and it's backed by a long 10-year/100,000-mile powertrain warranty. Because it has the best combination of quality and value in its class, we named the Tucson our 2024 Best Compact SUV for the Money.

2023 vs. 2024 Hyundai Tucson: What's the Difference?
The big change for 2024 is that the sporty N Line model moves over to the Tucson hybrid lineup (reviewed separately), swapping out its gas-only engine for a turbocharged gas-electric powertrain. Hyundai also brings standard haptic steering wheel feedback to the new Tucson. With this, the steering wheel vibrates if the vehicle starts to drift from its lane or might collide with a car in its blind spot.

The 2024 Hyundai Tucson N Line combines a cushy ride, a roomy, refined interior and sophisticated tech. It has all you want in a modern compact SUV, except speed.

2차전지는 우리가 스마트폰을 사용하는 시간에 따라 충전능력이 떨어지듯이,
하이브리드(전기차 포함) 자동차도 사용시간(주로 충방전, 충전 및 운행 횟수)에 맞춰 충전량이 줄어들기에,
약 5년정도면 우리가 스마트폰 빳데리 용량줄듯이 연비가 극히 나빠집니다.

한국 공업규격에 따르면,
2차전지의 생산시 생산LOT별 샘플에 대한 충방전를 500회 했을시,
초기 충전량의 75%이상이면 양품으로 처리합니다.
